{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_hines_ver01/data/sn83045462/0028065968A/1927032701/0243.xml":{"full_text":"14\nBASINS SUGGESTED\nAS BATHING POOLS\nAbandoned Reservoir May\nBe Converted for Use\nof Swimmers.\nthe time approaching when\nthe Water Department will abandon\nthe Brightwood Reservoir at Sixteenth\nand Kennedy streets, officials will\nturn their attention before the end\nof this year to the question of what\nis to be done with the two large\nbasins after they have been drained\nfor the last time.\nAlthough the reservoir will be elimi\nnated from active service as a storage\npoint for water some time in July,\nwhen it will be superseded by a por\ntion of the newly built supply sys\ntem, It is the intention of J. S. Gar\nland, superintendent of the District\nWater Department, to hold the Bright\nwood basins in readiness to be used\nfor several months after July, until\nthe new supply lines have been tried\nthoroughly in actual operation.\nMay Be Bathing Center.\nPreliminary and informal discussion\namong officials of the District govern\nment and the National Capital Tark\nand Planning Commission has cen\ntered chiefly on the suggestion that\nthe old reservoir be converted into\nswimming pools as a part of the out\ndoor recreational system of the office\nof public buildings and public Mirks.\nInasmuch as the reservoir will not\nba obsolete for water supply purposes\nuntil the end of this Summer, there i\nis nothing to be gained by a decision\nat this time and indications are the\nproblem will be gone into carefully\nbetween now and next year.\nIf it should be decided that It\nis desirable to make use of the reser\nvair basins in connection with public\nrecreational facilities the first step\nprobably would be to arrange for their\ntransfer to the office of public build\nings and parks. The reservoir now\nbelongs to the District Water Depart\nment.\nChange Seen as Costly.\nWhile the problem would not be one\nfor his office to settle unless such a\ntransfer should be made, Lieut. Col.\ntT. S. Grant, 3d, director of public\nbuildings and parks, recently made\nsome observations of the reservoir.\nHis impressions led him to believe\nthat the converting of the two basins\ninto swimming pools would not be as\nsimple and inexpensive a project as\nwould appear at first glance.\nEach basin of the reservoir is 300\nfeet wide, 415 feet long and more\nthan 20 feet in depth. Col. Grant in\ndicated he regarded the depth of the\nbasins as an obstacle to be overcome\nif it should be decided to make swim\nming pools out of them. He said he\nhad given some thought to the possi\nbility of constructing false bottoms\nthat would raise the level. He said\nit would require a considerable out\nlay of funds to make such a change.\nIf they were used as pools with the\nwater at the present bottom and with\nthe necessary locker facilities above,\nCol. Grant believes they would be\ntoo hot for comfortable use in Sum\nmer because of the depth. All of\nthese factors, it was indicated, will\nhave to be gone into before a deter\nmination is reached.\nWOMEN WILL RENEW\nFIGHT FOR SUFFRAGE\nFair Workers Will Appeal to\n\u201cYounger Set\u201d in French\nSenate.\nSr the Associated Press.\nPARIS, March 26. \u2014The younger set\nof French Senators\u2014those whose ages\nrun between 40 and 60\u2014will come in\nfor a lot of feminine attention right\nafter the Easter recess ends.\nAssurances to this effect were given\nthe Associated Press today by deter\nmined suffragist leaders who are still\nunconvinced that the cause of \u201cvotes\nfor women\u201d is lost despite the reverse\nit suffered this week. Yesterday a\nSenate committee voted to report un\nfavorably on Senator Louis Martin\u2019s\nbill giving women the right to vote\nand to hold public office. Nevertheless,\nthe suffragists say they are sure they\ncan raise senatorial majority in their\nfavor if the more youthful-minded\n\u2022olons are properly cultivated.\n\u201cWe expected the committee\u2019s de\ncision,\u201d Mme. Mallaterre-Senier, chief\nof the Catholic feminist group, said\ntoday, \u201cbut all we ask of Senator Mar\nraud (who will present the committee\u2019s\nfindings) is to bring his report before\nthe Senate soon after Easter so i: can\nbe acted on before the long vacation,\nbeginning about July 14. We are sure\nthat the new blood Injected into the\nupper body by the January elections,\nat which one-third of Its membership\nwas renewed, will respond to our ap\npeal. We don\u2019t care whether this re\nport Is unfavorable.\u201d\nMELLON PREDICTS NO\nLET-UP IN PROSPERITY\nBusiness to Continue Good, Secre\ntary Says on Departure\nfor Europe.\nBy the Awsw-iated Prese.\nNEW YORK. March 26.\u2014Secretary\nof the Treasury Andrew Mellon, who\n\u2022ailed for Europe early today on the\nsteamship Olympic, expressed opti\nmism on the business outlook.\n\"I see nothing to indicate that busi\nness will not continue to be good\nthroughout the country,\u201d he said.\n\u201cThe stock market seems to be going\nalong in a very orderly fashion, and\nI see no evidences of overspeculation.\n\u201cThere is an abundant supply of\neasy money throughout the country,\nwhich should take <a re of any con\ntingencies that might arise. 1 do not\nlook for any change in the Federal\nreserve rediscount rate for some time\nto come, because I can see ruo occa\nsion for changing it. Brokers\u2019 loans\ngive a very good insight Into the\nstock market situation, and they ap\npear in a very healthy state.\n\u201cThe Government will have about\n1500.000,000 surplus on hand as of June\n30. but I cannot say what the next\ntongress will do toward lowering\ntaxes.\"\nIrrigation Puling' Appealed.\nThe Verde River Irrigation and\nRower District of Arizona, yesterday\nappealed to the District Supreme\nI'ourt from a decision of Justice Staf\nford of the District Supreme Court\ndenying its application for an in\njunction against Secretary of the In\nterior Work and Commissioner Spry\ncf the General Land Office. The plain\ntiff seeks to enjoin the officials from\ncanceling its application for rights\nof way for reservoirs and canals for\nIrrigation purposes in the Salt River\nValley of Arizona.\nAttorney Edwin L. Wilson appears\nlor the company.\nBasle, Switzerland, has issued spe\ncial poster stamps to commemorate\nthis year's exhibition of Swiss in\ndustries.\nGEORGETOWN SINGERS IN DEBUT TONIGHT\njBI' ip ssL |ohs|\u00a3L Jrl? f^.\n||pKp* jhE* f fiPlfflisKitf' v\npmf\u00dfKwrasw Mgy **W-'\n-W(il\u00bbl|pMillffll|jy\nGeorgetown University Glee Club, which will give its first concert tonight at Gaston Hall. Edward O. Donovan, director; Richard M. McKcon, S. G.j\nmoderator.\nROTHSCHILD PLEA\nFOR SLUE SKY LAW\nBusiness Bureau Head Cites\nNeed for Restraining\n\u201cTrick\u201d Promoting.\nVoicing gratification over the an\nnounced intention of Senator Capper\nof Kansas to seek early enactment of\na blue sky law for the District of\nColumbia, Louis Rothschild, director\nof the Better Business Bureau, last\nnight in a radio address over WMAL,\nsounded a warning that the Spring\ncampaign of promoters of \u201cquestion\nable\u2019\u2019 sales schemes now is on.\nMr. Rothschild described a number\nof sales schemes recently imported\nhere, which he said were misleading\nand .questionable id character. One\nof them, \u201can old one practiced by\nfake stock promoters.\u201d now is flourish\ning in this city, he said.\nMany such promoters, driven from\nother sections of the country, now\nfind no legal handicap to their opera\ntions here, he pointed out.\nNo Barrier in District.\n\"There is no law in the District\nof Columbia to stop this flood of ques\ntionable securities,\u201d said Mr. Roths\nchild. \"We note with gratification a\nrecent statement by Senator Capper\nthat he is going to push a so-called\nblue-sky law for Washington. It cer\ntainly is needed.\n\u201cIn the meanwhile, the only protec\ntion here now is In following the\nslogan, 'Before you invest\u2014investi\ngate.\u2019\n\u201cA stock salesman informed the\nBetter Business Bureau this week\nthat in one month 38 different pro\nmotions w\u2019ere offered to him for sale\nand that not one of them would pass\nproper investigation. This number\nindicates the enormous amount of\nworthless paper offered to the people\nof Washington under the guise of\n\u2018investments.\u2019\nMajority Held Honest.\nDespite the operations of the \u201cGet\nRich Quick Wallingfords.\u201d however,\nMr. Rothschild pointed out, \u201cthe vast\nmajority of securities are funda\nmentally honest and salesmen of this\ntype are a proper part of our business\nlife, performing a real service.\n\u201cYou will not get the idea,\u201d he con\ncluded, \u201cthat all stocks are worthless\nand all salesmen of securities are\nquestionable schemers. But there are\nenough unscrupulous ones, however,\nto recommend that the people of\nWashington be cautious In making\ninvestments.\u201d\nThe speaker offered the services of\nthe Better Business Bureau in making\ninvestigations of sales promotions of\nquestionable character.\nFLYERS LEAvTpANAMA\nON GOOD-WILL MISSION\nLieutenants Go to Join Planes Now\nReturning Prom South\nAmerican Tour.\nBy the A\u00bb*oei\u00bbted Pres.\nPANAMA, March 26.\u2014Lieuts. Leon\nard D. Weddington and Ennis C.\nWhitehead of the United States Army\ngood-will flight took off from France\nField this morning for Maracay, Vene\nzuela. They are en route to Join the\nother good-will flyers who left Cayenne\ntoday for Paramibo, Dutch Guiana.\nThe recent crash of the good-will\nplanes at Buenos Aires in which two\nflyers perished left the good will flight\nwith only three planes and four sur\nviving crews. Accordingly Lieuts.\nWeddington and Whitehead crossed\nSouth America to Chile, where they\nembarked for Panama to obtain a new\nplane and rejoin the other flyers w r ho\nare following the scheduled itinerary\nup to the east coast of South\nAmerica.\nFearson Obtains Writ.\nJustice Hitz of the District Supreme\nCourt, has granted a writ of habeas\ncorpus to Robert Lee Fearson, Jr.,\nwho was arrested Friday by the\npolice at the request of Maryland\nauthorities, who charge him with\ndriving while Intoxicated and collid\ning. in Maryland about a year ago.\nFearson was released on a bond of\nSSOO for a hearing scheduled for April\n15.\nmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmn i\nRare\nEuropean Cheese\nat\nCenter Market\nHouses For Safe sad Reai\nJ. Leo Kolb\nWAIN 5027\n\u2022B Nsw York At. 1237 Wtee\u2019s. Am\nExpert Watch Repairing\nGEO. W. SPIER\nJeweler\n310 *<h St. N.W.\nWi Speelslire In Perfect Diamond*\nand Fine Wateliee\nThirty-erven Tear* in One Location\nTHE SUNDAY STAR, WASHINGTON, D. C, MARCH 27, 1027-PART 1.\nCAVAIR PRICE LOWERED.\nFRENCH LICK, Ind., March 26\n(>P).\u2014Cavair, aristocrat of the dinner\nrelishes, sells in America now for half\nwhat it cost before the Bolshevists\nbecame the ruling element In Russia.\nThe reason? Because the Soviet\nregime has permitted more Russians\nto fish the Caspian Sea for sturgeon,\nwhich yield cavair, according to Paul\nPerreau, Western manager of an\nAmerican importing house. Cavair\nsold in New York for sl4 a pound in\n1917, while today it is $7.\nNew Yorkers are the largest con\nsumers of cavair, with Chicago sec\nond, said Perreau, who is spending\na few days here.\nCHARITYSWINDLERS\nINVADE CHURCH FIELD\nFather Walsh Says Some Pose as\nPriests\u2014More Than SIOO,OOO\nDishonestly Collected.\nI\nBogus alms collectors are preying\nupon the public in connection with\nvarious Catholic charities, Rev. Ed\nmund A. Walsh, president of the\nCatholic Near East Welfare Associa\ntion, said last night.\nContributions for relief in Russia\nand the Near East, Father Walsh said,\nshould be sent to the office of the as\nsociation at 480 Lexington avenue,\nNew York, and not entrusted to indi\nvidual collectors.\nHe estimates that the swindlers to\ndate have secured more than SIOO,OOO.\nSome of them have gone so far as to\npose as visiting priests. Several have\nbeen arrested.\nThe Catholic Near East Welfare\nAssociation, Father Walsh said, is en\ngaged in putting into effect the Holy\nSee\u2019s program of rehabilitation and\nreconstruction in Turkey, Green-,\nArmenia, Syria and the Balkans, in\ncluding the maintenance of schools,\norphanages and refugee settlements.\nIt also is planning to place a number\nof Russiair youths in American col\nleges.\nBarber Ross, Inc.\nThe Big Hardware and Hoasefurnishinga Store\n11th and G Streets\nSeeger and White Mountain\nRefrigerators\u20143rd floor\nHousehold Refrigerator, 3-door\n1 style, hardwood case, white en\nameled; iee capacity, (?1 O CA\n60 lbs OAO.OU\nNesco Oil Cook Stove, oTtukr Tri\u00abn\u00bbu\nwith blue gras flame. Manning Bmv\nStove, $17.35; P w,th adr man Electric Iron,\nwith \u00aba hi net, $22.00 JuKtabo handl 6 -lb. size, nickel\n3- Stove, $22.00; Special,\nwith cabinet, $28.50 A<v plated. Complete\n4- etove, $28.00; {Of* with stand C*Q AA\nwith cabinet, $36.00 and cord \u00abPO*UU\nMetal Waste KHchen Seta of\nPaper Baaket, P\"\u201d S ga r\nassorted colors. Can. Tea and\nptl P _ -.zaW\u00dff Coffee Can: fin\nnicely decorated\nin assorted >shed in blue and\nstyles. 12 Blssell Standard Car-\nin. high pet Sweeper, oo mp* Cftr*\nguaranteed QO*iO vUV* Jvl\nHumphrey T l henn^ x\nwith seven |B9j[j|jj||j{rj\u00df tachable to\nra<l ia HBSHH9I any\nReduced to socket W\nHAIR SAID 10 SHOW\nRAGE, SEX AND AGE\nChicago University Student\nGives Conclusions From\nDetailed Experiments.\nBy the Associated Press.\nCHICAGO, March 26.\u2014Human hair\nbetrays race, nationality, sex and\nprobably age, the American Anthro\npological Association of Central\nUnited States was informed at its\nannual meeting here today by Morris\nBernstein of New York City, a student\nat the University of Chicago, who\nhas concluded detailed experiments\nwith hair of all colors and coarseness.\nAn Irishman\u2019s hair, for instance,\nhas different weight from an Italian\u2019s,\nand an old Irishman\u2019s hair, Mr. Bern\nstein said he believed, would show a\ndefinite difference from a young Irish\nman\u2019s.\nThis discovery has considerable im\nportance in the realm of physical\nanthropology, Bernstein said, inas\nmuch as researchers may now have\nhair to work upon as well as skulls\nin making anthropological determina\ntions.\n\u201cDifferences in hair weight are due\nto three causes,\u201d he said, \u201cfirst, dif\nferences in quantity of pigment\npresent; second, presence or absence\nof air bubbles; and third, differences\nin area of cross section, that Is,\ngERENS LUNCH\n62$ E St N.W.\nQuality*Food. Low Prices |j\ncoarseness of hair. Sexual differences\nseem to be due to the differences in\narea of cross-section.\u201d\np\u00bb- iph\"\" inr= \u2014ini==ini=ini ini= inf====inr===n\n\u25a0*l\nKaufmann\u2019s\u2014A National Institution of 21 Stores\nt None\nElectric Waffle Set; I\nJ V. Famous \"Quality Brand\u201d 5-Piece Waffle Service. V\nZ-T;*wl\u00bb7*. Makes delicious waffles right at table\u2014piping hot, _ I pi\nD nigruy golden brown, thick and tender\u2014with rich, crisp, flaky Fully r\nISlirLoloJ crusts and \"melt away\u201d insides. Just as fast as you can\nIVlCKelea eat. No Smoke! No Odor! Extra deep grids require QuCLrCMteed\nWafflp no greasing! And never a waffle sticks! Double Heat* tt\nmg Element bakes both sides at once. Cord and plug tiCCtting\nIrOTl included. Complete with Lovely Panelled Aluminum r\u00abi _\nl J One Pint Syrup Pitcher, Sugar Shaker, 2 Qt. Batter ElCmCtlt E\nA Pitcher and Large Round Tray.\nThis 5-Piece Electric Waffle Set has never before been sold for\nless than $16.00. Ten Weeks to Pay! No Red Tape! No\nDelays! Only a limited number of sets will be sold. Don\u2019t F\nwait for the Big Rush. Be Here Early Monday Morning!\nj ONLY\nj An Example of $0.75 1 A Weeks\nOur Budget Plan S CES 1U to Pay\ni psEI Kaufmann\u2019s r~ 11\nI-- 1415 H STREET N-W. I\n31 --JE1E5555313C1\u2014--PBL. lI3EIEHZII\